WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:16.632
Everything so far ranked single moves. But what if you ran
several of them together? Combining moves stacks more
trades into every day, and that can pass an evaluation
faster, and smoother, than any one move could alone.

2
00:00:17.232 --> 00:00:28.008
This is Best Basket to Flip. It searches for the best
combination of moves to run as a single basket. More
trades per day means you reach the target sooner, with the
day-to-day bumps averaged out.

3
00:00:28.608 --> 00:00:40.416
The Best ROI basket combines the moves for the most net
profit per dollar spent. Notice it might pick three or
four moves that, run side by side, simply earn more per
dollar than any of them on their own.

4
00:00:41.016 --> 00:00:51.960
The Fastest-Payout basket combines the moves that reach
your first withdrawal soonest. Stacking trades from
several moves means more chances to hit target each day,
so the payout clock runs faster.

5
00:00:52.560 --> 00:01:03.144
And the Cheapest basket reaches net-positive with the
fewest accounts and resets. The smallest possible spend to
get the combined engine paying for itself. Often just two
carefully paired moves.

6
00:01:03.744 --> 00:01:15.888
There's a real catch though. A basket only helps if the
moves don't all lose on the same day. That's exactly what
the Portfolio step checks. So treat the basket as the
speed play, and let correlation be the safety check.

7
00:01:16.488 --> 00:01:21.168
One move is a plan. The right basket is a faster, smoother
road to funded.
